center for medieval and early modern studies skip to main content home login center for medieval and early modern studies enter your keywords main menu about programs courses people blogs news calendar resources you are here home the role of history in a liberal education reflections on the 2012 study of undergraduate education at stanford presenter james campbell stanford university part of the teaching history matters lecture series professor campbell is the edgar e robinson professor in united states history at stanford university his talk will be based upon his recent work as co chair of the study of undergraduate education at stanford sues committee and the reform of the undergraduate curriculum including changes to the ihum program you are invited to read the report of the sues committee in advance but it is not required it can be downloaded at sues stanford edu teaching history matters invites teachers to speak about history curricula and teaching strategies that tas don t often encounter at stanford these speakers will offer practical advice for candidates in a competitive job market who need to understand public university curricula and discuss teaching philosophy for tas these events will supply a broad view on opportunities to teach and techniques to engage audiences in diverse settings all graduate students are encouraged to attend recent grads and professors are welcome refreshments will be served for more information suzanne duchacek srsuther stanford edu date february 21 2012 4 00pm 5 30pm location history corner 200 307 center for medieval and early modern studies pigott hall building 260 450 serra mall stanford ca 94350 director cecile alduy alduy stanford edu web manager biliana kassabova bilianak stanford edu follow cmemsstanford facebook contact map & directions
